</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFF4FFB5FF3D9A2A68047B86" blockId="25.[151,756,1581,1767]" pageId="25" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFF4FFB5FF3D9A2A68C47BE7" bold="true" box="[151,457,1646,1670]" pageId="25" pageNumber="39">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It was first described from the Late Cretaceous of 
<collectingRegion id="8818F811FFF4FFB5FE039ACA6B147BC7" box="[425,537,1678,1702]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="25" pageNumber="39">California</collectingRegion>
. In the study area, it is rarely found in the Maastrichtian and Paleocene sediments.
</paragraph>
